docs.abstract: A meat-lovers guide to eating less meat. Dax Shepard is listening. Remembering David Stern. Martin Scorsese is letting go. And more.
docs.snippet: A meat-lovers guide to eating less meat. Dax Shepard is listening. Remembering David Stern. Martin Scorsese is letting go. And more.
docs.lead_paragraph: Welcome to the first weekend of 2020! We’ve started the year with an airstrike in Iraq that killed a top commander from Iran, raging wildfires in Australia and an attack of tumbleweeds in Washington State. These are some stories you may have missed in the whirlwind of news. So grab a big mug of tea and enjoy.

docs.abstract: The death of Qassim Suleimani strengthened the hand of hard-liners, experts say, and undermined those who have tried to normalize relations with the West.
docs.snippet: The death of Qassim Suleimani strengthened the hand of hard-liners, experts say, and undermined those who have tried to normalize relations with the West.
docs.lead_paragraph: In cities across Iran, tens of thousands packed the streets to mourn Maj. Gen. Qassim Suleimani. Black-clad women and men beat their chests and clutched photos of him. A black flag went up on the golden dome of Imam Reza shrine in the city of Mashhad, one of the holiest sites of Shiite Islam.

headline.main: Iranians Close Ranks Behind Leaders After U.S. Kills Popular General
headline.print_headline: Iran, Divided Politically, Unites In Its Hostility Toward America

docs.snippet: In 1945, Giichi Matsumura left the infamous Japanese-American internment camp to paint in the Sierra Nevada and never returned.
docs.lead_paragraph: Nearly 75 years ago, Giichi Matsumura left the grounds of the Manzanar War Relocation Center in California with a group of fishermen who had set out for the lakes of the Sierra Nevada.

headline.print_headline: After 74 Years, Family to Claim Remains  Of Japanese Man Interred at U.S. Camp

docs.abstract: Chani Nicholas doesn’t want to tell you who you are, but who you can be.
docs.snippet: Chani Nicholas doesn’t want to tell you who you are, but who you can be.
docs.lead_paragraph: The first time I met up with the astrologer Chani Nicholas in Los Angeles, in December, it was for a lunch interview. We sipped our drinks and chewed truffle French fries; I asked questions and she answered them. The conversation flowed easily. We laughed a lot.

headline.main: Your Favorite Internet Astrologer Wrote a Book
headline.print_headline: An Astrologer for the Internet Era

docs.abstract: The comic is returning to host the awards show a fifth time. Here’s a look at his most memorable moments.
docs.snippet: The comic is returning to host the awards show a fifth time. Here’s a look at his most memorable moments.
docs.lead_paragraph: Ricky Gervais will return to host the 2020 Golden Globes on Sunday, and once again no one will be safe. Not the nominees. Not the Hollywood Foreign Press Association, the group that sponsors the awards. And not even NBC, which broadcasts them.

headline.main: Ricky Gervais at the Golden Globes: Laughs, Gasps and Cringes

docs.abstract: Officials across three states braced for what they feared could be the worst day yet of Australia’s disastrous fire season.
docs.snippet: Officials across three states braced for what they feared could be the worst day yet of Australia’s disastrous fire season.
docs.lead_paragraph: Hundreds of people who had spent days trapped by fires along a beach in the town of Mallacoota reached safety more than 300 miles away on Saturday morning, after a 20-hour trip on a naval ship.

headline.main: Australia Fires Keep Spreading as Military Reservists Called Up
